quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  18,28,"Keep yourself attached to those who call on their Lord, morning and evening, seeking His pleasure; and do not let your eyes turn away from them, desiring the attraction of worldly life; and do not obey one whose heart We have made heedless of Our remembrance, one who pursues his own whims and becomes dissolute"
  18,29,"Say, \"This is the truth from your Lord. Let him who will, believe in it, and him who will, deny it.\" For the wrongdoers We have prepared a Fire which will cover them like a canopy, and if they beg for water, they will be given water as hot as molten lead, which will scald their faces: how dreadful a drink, and how evil a resting place"
  18,30,"As for those who believe and do good deeds, We do not let the reward of anyone who does a good deed go to waste"
  18,31,"they shall dwell in the Gardens of eternity where rivers flow at their feet. Reclining upon raised couches, they will be adorned with bracelets of gold, and will wear green robes of fine silk and heavy brocade. An excellent reward and an excellent resting place"
  18,32,"Recite to them the parable of two men! One of them We provided with two vineyards which We surrounded with date-palms, and placed a field of grain in between"
  18,33,each garden produced its fruit and did not fail to yield its best; We even caused a river to gush forth in the midst of them
  18,34,"and so he had fruit in abundance. While conversing with his companion, he said, \"I am wealthier than you are, and have a bigger following"